Algorithm BruteForce_Undirected(P)
Input: A set P of n points (x, y).
Output: A list of unordered line segments (edges) that form the convex hull boundary.

Edges ← EmptyList

for i ← 1 to n do
    for j ← i + 1 to n do
        allLeft ← true
        allRight ← true

        for k ← 1 to n do
            if k ≠ i and k ≠ j then
                side_value ← (Pj.x - Pi.x) * (Pk.y - Pi.y) - (Pj.y - Pi.y) * (Pk.x - Pi.x)

                if side_value < 0 then
                    allLeft ← false
                if side_value > 0 then
                    allRight ← false

                if not allLeft and not allRight then
                    break

        if allLeft or allRight then
            Add the segment {Pi, Pj} to Edges

return Edges
